1
00:00:04,166 --> 00:00:05,500
(Previously)
Get out of my shop.

2
00:00:06,133 --> 00:00:07,766
And don't ever set foot in here again.

3
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:13,300
By the way, where's Bom?

4
00:00:13,866 --> 00:00:14,966
He's with his new wife.

5
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:17,366
So why don't you take a break?

6
00:00:17,666 --> 00:00:19,400
Go to a temple, pray for some good luck.

7
00:00:19,733 --> 00:00:21,066
They say this place...

8
00:00:21,566 --> 00:00:22,366
is really powerful.

9
00:00:22,733 --> 00:00:23,733
Wish for a job, you get a job.

10
00:00:24,266 --> 00:00:25,333
Wish for money, you get money.

11
00:00:25,766 --> 00:00:26,900
Wish for a husband, you get a husband.

12
00:00:36,066 --> 00:00:37,100
Then we can go together.

13
00:00:37,566 --> 00:00:38,733
I came alone, too.

14
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:42,100
My name is Erng.

15
00:00:42,466 --> 00:00:43,500
My name is Intha.

16
00:00:43,766 --> 00:00:45,000
You can just call me In.

17
00:00:45,300 --> 00:00:46,814
So, what are you praying for?

18
00:00:46,814 --> 00:00:47,700
For Work.

19
00:00:48,366 --> 00:00:49,166
Opening The bar

20
00:00:49,933 --> 00:00:50,733
make a lot of money?

21
00:00:51,766 --> 00:00:53,200
Can I take over your bar?

22
00:00:53,700 --> 00:00:54,500
I'm not selling.

23
00:00:54,733 --> 00:00:56,043
But if you see the bar...

24
00:00:56,043 --> 00:00:57,800
and you're okay with being a partner,

25
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:01,133
I'll draft a contract and send it for you to sign.

26
00:01:01,466 --> 00:01:02,266
Deal.

27
00:01:02,666 --> 00:01:03,466
If you're in

28
00:01:04,066 --> 00:01:04,866
I'm also in

29
00:01:05,166 --> 00:01:05,966
Send it over.

30
00:01:06,966 --> 00:01:08,066
If I'm lame,

31
00:01:09,066 --> 00:01:10,333
doesn't that make you ancient?

32
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:12,166
Which hotel are you staying at?

33
00:01:15,533 --> 00:01:16,866
Are you sure about this?

34
00:01:18,566 --> 00:01:19,366
Yeah.

35
00:01:19,766 --> 00:01:21,366
A whole new world.

36
00:01:22,766 --> 00:01:23,700
It's not the first time.

37
00:01:27,066 --> 00:01:27,866
May I?

38
00:02:13,766 --> 00:02:14,600
May I?

39
00:02:42,733 --> 00:02:43,733
What happened to you?

40
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:47,866
My ex-husband beat me up.

41
00:02:49,566 --> 00:02:50,533
You're a big guy.

42
00:02:52,266 --> 00:02:53,533
Didn't you fight back?

43
00:02:56,566 --> 00:02:57,366
I'm small.

44
00:02:58,900 --> 00:03:00,566
Can you please pretend I'm small?

45
00:03:02,533 --> 00:03:03,866
Pretend I'm cute.

46
00:03:08,930 --> 00:03:09,766
Mmm.

47
00:03:11,484 --> 00:03:12,715
My little one.

48
00:04:52,491 --> 00:04:55,357
What the hell is happening to my life?

49
00:04:55,357 --> 00:04:56,962
Let me recap.

50
00:04:56,962 --> 00:04:58,112
My husband dumped me.

51
00:04:58,112 --> 00:05:00,136
Got a temple trip with a free stay.

52
00:05:00,362 --> 00:05:01,800
Met a guy named Intha.

53
00:05:02,433 --> 00:05:04,062
Hooked up with him last night.

54
00:05:08,191 --> 00:05:09,991
What more could I ask for?

55
00:05:14,091 --> 00:05:15,091
Whatever.

56
00:05:17,025 --> 00:05:19,158
But that guy isn't bad at all.

57
00:05:19,991 --> 00:05:20,991
He's got good moves.

58
00:05:23,225 --> 00:05:24,391
A good top.

59
00:05:27,525 --> 00:05:29,958
He even folded my
clothes before he left.

60
00:05:31,158 --> 00:05:32,991
But he seems pretty stingy.

61
00:05:33,625 --> 00:05:35,325
Didn't leave a single thing behind.

62
00:05:45,358 --> 00:05:46,558
Sorry for going through your bag.

63
00:05:46,958 --> 00:05:47,891
I laid out a shirt for you.

64
00:05:48,558 --> 00:05:50,125
Today's lucky color is white.

65
00:05:56,570 --> 00:06:00,845
Sorry I left before you woke up.

66
00:06:00,845 --> 00:06:03,432
I tried to wake you, but you wouldn't get up.

67
00:06:03,432 --> 00:06:05,991
I had a really good time last night.

68
00:06:08,425 --> 00:06:10,464
I don't do one-night stands.

69
00:06:10,464 --> 00:06:12,690
I'm serious.

70
00:06:12,690 --> 00:06:15,438
I don't know if this sounds weird,

71
00:06:15,438 --> 00:06:16,926
since we just met.

72
00:06:16,926 --> 00:06:17,697
But...

73
00:06:18,888 --> 00:06:20,983
I like you.

74
00:06:20,983 --> 00:06:23,480
I'll see you at the bar on Sunday.

75
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:26,430
Also, I'm not the type to hit and quit.

76
00:06:26,430 --> 00:06:28,430
I'll take responsibility.

77
00:06:29,635 --> 00:06:30,840
But today, I have to attend a Kathina ceremony.

78
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:31,734
Don't forget to wear the lucky color shirt

79
00:06:31,734 --> 00:06:32,840
I picked out for you.

80
00:06:34,091 --> 00:06:34,891
A Kathina ceremony.

81
00:06:35,558 --> 00:06:36,525
A Kathina ceremony?

82
00:07:28,100 --> 00:07:35,600
"ChermChey" (Episode 2)

83
00:07:55,391 --> 00:07:56,891
Then why the hell didn't you reply to my texts?

84
00:07:57,558 --> 00:07:59,758
I told you I'd come to the bar on Sunday.

85
00:08:09,558 --> 00:08:10,691
This car is pink.

86
00:08:11,125 --> 00:08:12,425
It's an eyesore.

87
00:08:13,958 --> 00:08:15,991
My Benz's understated style is better.

88
00:08:16,991 --> 00:08:17,825
That one's the senior.

89
00:08:18,125 --> 00:08:19,191
Erng's is the junior.

90
00:08:19,558 --> 00:08:20,725
It's a good deal.

91
00:08:31,491 --> 00:08:32,931
Forest.

92
00:10:09,758 --> 00:10:10,837
Nok?

93
00:10:11,696 --> 00:10:12,590
What's up?

94
00:10:14,431 --> 00:10:15,463
Who's Nok?

95
00:10:16,091 --> 00:10:17,081
Nok Yollada?

96
00:10:18,325 --> 00:10:20,591
I'm in bed. I'm not getting up.

97
00:10:25,291 --> 00:10:26,091
Oh.

98
00:10:28,825 --> 00:10:29,625
Oh.

99
00:10:31,091 --> 00:10:31,891
Brother

100
00:10:33,291 --> 00:10:34,625
I thought you were going to kick me.

101
00:10:35,625 --> 00:10:36,425
It's me.

102
00:10:40,191 --> 00:10:40,991
Uh...

103
00:10:43,025 --> 00:10:43,825
Sunday.

104
00:10:44,725 --> 00:10:46,491
You said you'd come on Sunday, right?

105
00:10:47,391 --> 00:10:48,191
Sorry.

106
00:10:48,591 --> 00:10:49,825
I thought you were one of my employees.

107
00:10:57,125 --> 00:10:58,091
What time is it?

108
00:10:58,758 --> 00:11:00,358
I don't know where my phone is.

109
00:11:03,925 --> 00:11:04,725
1:30 PM.

110
00:11:05,958 --> 00:11:08,325
1:30? I usually wake up at 3 PM.

111
00:11:12,925 --> 00:11:14,791
Sorry for waking you up, then.

112
00:11:15,958 --> 00:11:17,091
What about my contract?

113
00:11:25,158 --> 00:11:26,469
Chill out.

114
00:11:26,831 --> 00:11:27,998
I just woke up.

115
00:11:28,631 --> 00:11:30,051
Give me some time.

116
00:11:33,158 --> 00:11:34,925
So that means there's no contract, right?

117
00:11:38,958 --> 00:11:40,358
Can you stop looking so fierce?

118
00:11:41,291 --> 00:11:42,725
Yeah, I'm fierce.

119
00:11:44,358 --> 00:11:45,951
If there's no contract...

120
00:11:47,624 --> 00:11:48,835
you can pay me with your body.

121
00:12:02,125 --> 00:12:02,925
Erng.

122
00:12:03,291 --> 00:12:04,425
Did you fall back asleep?

123
00:12:06,958 --> 00:12:07,758
Yeah.

124
00:12:08,825 --> 00:12:12,325
I'm just absorbing the merit from the body of
someone who attended a Kathina ceremony.

125
00:12:13,425 --> 00:12:13,925
Yeah.

126
00:12:13,925 --> 00:12:15,291
I brought you some merit.

127
00:12:16,825 --> 00:12:18,158
I was gone for several days.

128
00:12:19,091 --> 00:12:20,125
It was pretty crowded.

129
00:12:20,625 --> 00:12:21,891
But the temple was really far away.

130
00:12:22,925 --> 00:12:24,425
My phone had no signal at all.

131
00:12:24,891 --> 00:12:26,225
So I couldn't contact you.

132
00:12:27,025 --> 00:12:28,191
But everything I said,

133
00:12:29,791 --> 00:12:31,225
I meant every word of it.

134
00:12:35,358 --> 00:12:37,122
How serious and sincere were you?

135
00:12:37,981 --> 00:12:39,127
That's not important.

136
00:12:39,850 --> 00:12:42,760
But I want to know how important
that Kathina ceremony was.

137
00:12:46,025 --> 00:12:46,658
Important.

138
00:12:47,608 --> 00:12:48,886
Because my mom was the host.

139
00:12:50,288 --> 00:12:51,321
Did you know,

140
00:12:51,728 --> 00:12:53,263
the Kathina ceremony is
a special kind of merit-making?

141
00:12:54,258 --> 00:12:55,166
It only happens once a year.

142
00:12:57,225 --> 00:12:59,391
It's held for one month,
according to Buddhist precepts.

143
00:13:01,291 --> 00:13:02,291
The blessings are immense.

144
00:13:04,558 --> 00:13:05,691
I want to eat something

145
00:13:06,491 --> 00:13:07,291
I'm hungry.

146
00:13:08,558 --> 00:13:10,825
Did you bring me anything to eat?

147
00:13:12,491 --> 00:13:13,291
I did.

148
00:13:19,725 --> 00:13:21,091
But you're sleeping shirtless,

149
00:13:23,725 --> 00:13:25,158
and your door is unlocked.

150
00:13:29,958 --> 00:13:31,525
Are you trying to seduce me?

151
00:13:34,525 --> 00:13:35,525
If I were,

152
00:13:35,691 --> 00:13:37,191
Nok would've been my
husband a long time ago.

153
00:13:37,991 --> 00:13:38,958
Who is this Nok?

154
00:13:39,358 --> 00:13:40,158
My friend.

155
00:13:41,225 --> 00:13:42,025
I'm hungry.

156
00:13:43,925 --> 00:13:45,391
Are you really hungry?

157
00:13:45,825 --> 00:13:47,150
Yeah, I'm starving.

158
00:13:48,190 --> 00:13:49,623
I can smell the food so clearly.

159
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:53,696
My psychic senses tell me it's my breakfast.

160
00:14:00,091 --> 00:14:01,191
Barbecued pork noodles.

161
00:14:02,991 --> 00:14:05,358
I went to make merit with my family
this morning before coming here.

162
00:14:07,225 --> 00:14:08,591
So I bought some for you.

163
00:14:15,091 --> 00:14:15,925
No wonder.

164
00:14:18,525 --> 00:14:19,625
You're dressed so nicely.

165
00:14:30,391 --> 00:14:31,191
Brother

166
00:14:31,758 --> 00:14:33,225
Let me lie here for three minutes.

167
00:14:34,358 --> 00:14:35,291
It's so comfortable.

168
00:14:38,158 --> 00:14:39,325
Why don't you take off your shoes?

169
00:14:45,791 --> 00:14:47,291
Did you just push me?

170
00:14:48,325 --> 00:14:49,125
What?

171
00:14:49,758 --> 00:14:50,558
Huh?

172
00:14:50,725 --> 00:14:53,027
Why the harsh tone and the scary face?

173
00:14:53,479 --> 00:14:54,491
What are you going to do to me?

174
00:15:02,525 --> 00:15:04,158
Don't come any closer.

175
00:15:11,591 --> 00:15:12,725
What are you going to do?

176
00:15:18,725 --> 00:15:19,891
I'm going to eat you up.

177
00:15:24,325 --> 00:15:24,991
Don't.

178
00:15:25,579 --> 00:15:26,506
Don't you dare.

179
00:15:26,925 --> 00:15:27,725
Don't do it.

180
00:15:28,225 --> 00:15:29,025
No.

181
00:15:29,925 --> 00:15:30,725
Don't.

182
00:15:32,825 --> 00:15:33,625
Brother.

183
00:15:33,891 --> 00:15:35,041
Erng is scared now.

184
00:15:35,041 --> 00:15:36,425
Have mercy on Erng.

185
00:15:36,925 --> 00:15:37,791
Don't do it!

186
00:15:39,125 --> 00:15:39,925
Hey!

187
00:15:40,191 --> 00:15:41,291
Erng gives up.

188
00:15:42,025 --> 00:15:43,325
Don't do anything to Erng.

189
00:15:43,625 --> 00:15:44,425
Don't do anything.

190
00:15:45,225 --> 00:15:46,325
Don't do anything to me.

191
00:15:47,691 --> 00:15:48,491
Don't.

192
00:15:49,191 --> 00:15:49,991
Please don't.

193
00:15:50,425 --> 00:15:51,225
Stop

194
00:15:51,225 --> 00:15:51,725
Don't.

195
00:15:51,991 --> 00:15:53,091
Erng is scared now.

196
00:15:53,691 --> 00:15:54,491
Brother.

197
00:16:04,691 --> 00:16:06,291
Where can I take my shoes off?

198
00:16:07,225 --> 00:16:08,558
Take them off wherever you want.

199
00:16:14,825 --> 00:16:15,572
By the way,

200
00:16:15,889 --> 00:16:17,591
I saw a drink stall in front of your house.

201
00:16:17,817 --> 00:16:18,761
I'm a little thirsty.

202
00:16:19,304 --> 00:16:20,720
I'm getting a sweet drink.
Do you want anything?

203
00:16:22,358 --> 00:16:23,476
I'll have a lemon tea.

204
00:16:24,335 --> 00:16:26,470
But the old man takes a while.
Just a heads-up.

205
00:16:27,058 --> 00:16:27,725
Yeah, yeah.

206
00:16:33,791 --> 00:16:35,391
When you said you wanted to 'devour' me...

207
00:16:37,791 --> 00:16:39,291
You didn't mean anything else, right?

208
00:16:54,363 --> 00:16:56,592
I meant 'devour.' I said what I said.

209
00:16:57,958 --> 00:16:58,825
You sinner.

210
00:16:59,391 --> 00:17:00,425
Well, I'm your man anyway.

211
00:17:22,237 --> 00:17:24,237
Look up here

212
00:17:29,625 --> 00:17:30,125
Brother

213
00:17:30,628 --> 00:17:31,128
Brother

214
00:17:31,716 --> 00:17:32,216
What?

215
00:17:33,309 --> 00:17:34,812
Hurry up. We're going out.

216
00:17:46,291 --> 00:17:47,091
Where are you going?

217
00:17:48,891 --> 00:17:49,825
Just out.

218
00:17:51,558 --> 00:17:52,358
To the market.

219
00:17:54,325 --> 00:17:56,391
But let me show you the contract first.

220
00:17:57,025 --> 00:17:58,158
This is the old one.

221
00:17:58,491 --> 00:18:00,625
If you want to make any changes,
we can discuss them.

222
00:18:02,125 --> 00:18:03,158
Why do you need to go out?

223
00:18:04,225 --> 00:18:05,425
Stocking up on some things.

224
00:18:05,691 --> 00:18:07,958
When the shop's closed,
I plan to just stay in and watch movies.

225
00:18:08,525 --> 00:18:10,391
You can take the contract home to look at it.

226
00:18:10,558 --> 00:18:11,358
I'll look at it here.

227
00:18:11,625 --> 00:18:12,425
I'm not in a hurry.

228
00:18:13,325 --> 00:18:14,991
I don't have anywhere else to be.

229
00:18:16,725 --> 00:18:17,725
Want a cigarette?

230
00:18:20,491 --> 00:18:21,445
No, thanks.

231
00:18:21,807 --> 00:18:22,920
I don't feel like it.

232
00:18:25,491 --> 00:18:26,068
Brother

233
00:18:28,193 --> 00:18:29,919
What exactly are we?

234
00:18:36,625 --> 00:18:38,366
Whatever status

235
00:18:39,949 --> 00:18:41,342
you want us to be

236
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:47,891
I'm not ready to start over with anyone yet.

237
00:18:49,158 --> 00:18:50,025
Can you wait a little?

238
00:18:53,791 --> 00:18:55,325
I'm not in any rush.

239
00:18:57,725 --> 00:18:59,158
We can just see where this goes for now.

240
00:19:00,525 --> 00:19:02,025
You're not going to lead me on, are you?

241
00:19:03,158 --> 00:19:03,958
Let's find out.

242
00:19:09,158 --> 00:19:10,591
So, we're in the 'talking' stage.

243
00:19:11,391 --> 00:19:12,191
Okay.

244
00:19:12,291 --> 00:19:13,158
No, no.

245
00:19:14,325 --> 00:19:17,025
Let's go with 'convenience store' status.

246
00:19:18,591 --> 00:19:19,391
What are you talking about?

247
00:19:21,758 --> 00:19:24,191
You know, whenever you're hungry,
you can just stop by.

248
00:19:46,725 --> 00:19:48,125
You mean, to 'devour' each other?

249
00:19:48,325 --> 00:19:50,358
Damn, you're so blunt.

250
00:19:52,758 --> 00:19:53,825
I get hungry often.

251
00:19:55,391 --> 00:19:57,291
I'm open 24/7.

252
00:20:10,691 --> 00:20:11,753
I have a question.

253
00:20:14,240 --> 00:20:15,891
You're renting this place, right?

254
00:20:16,358 --> 00:20:16,944
Yeah.

255
00:20:17,487 --> 00:20:18,794
I want this place.

256
00:20:19,698 --> 00:20:20,893
Is the owner selling?

257
00:20:21,358 --> 00:20:23,331
Yeah, they're dying to sell it.

258
00:20:23,874 --> 00:20:25,375
The empty lot next door is for sale too.

259
00:20:26,053 --> 00:20:27,770
Because they're moving abroad for good.

260
00:20:29,125 --> 00:20:30,558
I've already started the paperwork to buy it.

261
00:20:30,758 --> 00:20:32,225
You know, to expand the shop.

262
00:20:33,025 --> 00:20:34,425
But now I don't have the money.

263
00:20:35,391 --> 00:20:37,291
So I was thinking of talking to them again...

264
00:20:37,525 --> 00:20:39,725
about just renting the shop
and the parking lot like before.

265
00:20:41,091 --> 00:20:42,491
Go ahead with the expansion.

266
00:20:42,991 --> 00:20:44,291
I just got more money.

267
00:20:45,325 --> 00:20:47,225
If you buy the house, where will I live?

268
00:20:47,625 --> 00:20:48,725
You'll live here, of course.

269
00:20:49,091 --> 00:20:50,825
I don't know the first thing about running a shop.

270
00:20:51,325 --> 00:20:52,558
So you can help me.

271
00:20:53,625 --> 00:20:56,025
And I'll just be here to throw money at the problems.

272
00:20:57,758 --> 00:20:59,725
My brother wants the condo I bought.

273
00:21:00,025 --> 00:21:01,091
I was planning to sell it anyway.

274
00:21:02,291 --> 00:21:04,025
I was going to use it as our marital home.

275
00:21:04,691 --> 00:21:05,891
But I don't need it anymore.

276
00:21:07,525 --> 00:21:09,358
So I can just let my brother have it.

277
00:21:09,925 --> 00:21:11,625
But I'll go talk to the owner for you.

278
00:21:12,758 --> 00:21:13,791
But the contract...

279
00:21:14,191 --> 00:21:15,325
we'll have to redo the whole thing.

280
00:21:15,525 --> 00:21:16,625
I have a friend who's a lawyer.

281
00:21:16,925 --> 00:21:18,391
I'll hire him to draft the contract.

282
00:21:18,891 --> 00:21:20,525
You really do like solving problems with money.

283
